)</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">trans</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">mul_le_of_le_one_left</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">apply</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">dist_nonneg</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Real</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">norm_eq_abs</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">abs_of_nonneg</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hb</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">      </span><span class=\"n\">linarith</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>I didn't see anything with both <code>hausdorffDist</code> and <code>segment</code> in mathlib</p>",
